%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20regret%20moving%20to%20Boulder%2C%20Colorado.%20I%20thought%20I'd%20fit%20right%20in%2C%20but%20it%20was%20the%20loneliest%20two%20years%20of%20my%20life.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221374%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amanda%20Loudin%20hiking%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64efae986f301e00193e8b00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221033%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmanda%20Loudin%20moved%20to%20Boulder%20because%20she%20loves%20being%20in%20and%20around%20the%20mountains%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20what%20she%20expected.%3Cp%3EAmanda%20Loudin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAmanda%20Loudin%20moved%20from%20Maryland%20to%20Boulder%2C%20Colorado%20but%20returned%20home%20after%20two%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EShe%20was%20lonely%20despite%20around%20outdoorsy%20people%20like%20herself%20and%20now%20realizes%20the%20move%20was%20impulsive.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EStaying%20in%20touch%20with%20her%20friends%20back%20home%20helped%20her%20get%20through%20the%20experience.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20an%20avid%20outdoors(wo)man.%20I%20love%20to%20hike%2C%20run%2C%20paddleboard%2C%20you%20name%20it%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20particularly%20love%20doing%20those%20activities%20in%20and%20around%20mountains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20you'd%20think%20a%20move%20from%20Maryland%20to%20Boulder%2C%20Colorado%20would've%20been%20the%20perfect%20match%20for%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%2C%20and%20after%20two%20years%2C%20I%20turned%20my%20car%20around%20and%20returned%20to%20Maryland.%20I%20have%20no%20regrets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMoving%20to%20Boulder%20wasn't%20what%20I%20expected%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20one%20of%20the%20many%20remote%20workers%20who%20took%20a%20leap%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20relocated.%20I%20always%20thought%20I'd%20retire%20in%20Colorado%2C%20but%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20move%20up%20my%20timeline%20and%20go%20now.%20My%20youngest%20was%20on%20board%2C%20so%20along%20with%20our%20dog%2C%20we%20packed%20up%20and%20headed%20west.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20Boulder%20is%20full%20of%20like-minded%2C%20outdoorsy%20people.%20But%20try%20as%20I%20might%2C%20I%20was%20never%20able%20to%20forge%20a%20community%20there%20on%20a%20level%20I%20had%20in%20the%20east.%20Maybe%20I%20should%20chalk%20it%20up%20to%20that%20whole%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2673-995X%2F2%2F1%2F1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BWestern%20individualism%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20those%20happy-with-life-as-long-as-they're-near-mountains%20types%2C%20community%20be%20damned%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20beer%20runs%2C%20a%20book%20club%2C%20and%20a%20pickleball%20league.%20I%20swam%20in%20the%20local%20reservoir%20with%20a%20master's%20swim%20group%2C%20hung%20out%20at%20local%20coffee%20shops%2C%20and%20more.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20none%20of%20it%20led%20to%20the%20community%20I%20craved.%20My%20neighbors%20didn't%20invite%20me%20to%20cookouts%2C%20I%20found%20no%20regular%20running%20groups%20that%20didn't%20require%20paying%20to%20play%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20fall%20into%20fun%20conversations%20at%20the%20dog%20park.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20people%20in%20Boulder%20are%20unfriendly%2C%20just%20different%20from%20what%20I'm%20used%20to%20in%20the%20mid-Atlantic%2C%20where%20I've%20lived%20my%20entire%20adult%20life.%20Here%20we%20seem%20to%20be%20very%20community-minded%2C%20and%20I%20have%20several%20groups%20of%20friends%20that%20revolve%20around%20a%20variety%20of%20shared%20interests.%20Even%20when%20we're%20not%20participating%20in%20those%20interests%2C%20we%20still%20get%20together%20to%20socialize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOut%20there%2C%20I%20think%20many%20people%20are%20pretty%20content%20on%20their%20own.%20If%20they're%20having%20a%20bad%20day%2C%20they%20go%20for%20a%20hike%20in%20the%20mountains.%20I%20can%20certainly%20appreciate%20that%2C%20but%20my%20choice%20would%20be%20a%20hike%20with%20a%20friend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20found%20my%20foothold%20in%20Boulder%20and%20returning%20to%20Maryland%20has%20felt%20like%20slipping%20on%20an%20old%20favorite%20hoodie%3A%20warm%2C%20secure%2C%20and%20familiar.%C2%A0%20Here%20are%20some%20lessons%20learned%20from%20my%20two-year%20move%20across%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20If%20you%20can%2C%20do%20some%20real%20time%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20a%20new%20location%20before%20committing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20work%2C%20I'd%20been%20to%20Boulder%20numerous%20times%20over%20the%20years%20leading%20up%20to%20my%20move%2C%20and%20even%20spent%20a%20full%20month%20there%20before%20packing%20the%20moving%20van%20six%20months%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20hindsight%2C%20however%2C%20I%20think%20the%20move%20was%20impulsive%20and%20that%20I%20didn't%20test%20the%20waters%C2%A0%20long%20enough.%20Even%20though%20I%20remote-worked%20there%20for%20that%20trial%20month%2C%20Boulder%20was%20still%20so%20sparkly%20and%20new%20to%20me%20that%20the%20time%20felt%20like%20a%20vacation.%20More%20time%20for%20%26quot%3Breal%20life%26quot%3B%20experience%E2%80%93efforts%20to%20find%20peers%20and%20friends%2C%20running%20partners%20and%20the%20like%20could%20have%20helped%20me%20learn%20it%20wasn't%20right%20for%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Don't%20move%20without%20a%20natural%20in-road%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wonder%20if%20things%20would%20have%20been%20different%20if%20I'd%20had%20younger%20children%2C%20or%20a%20job%20in%20an%20office.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20my%20move%2C%20my%20oldest%20was%20in%20college%20and%20my%20youngest%20was%20a%20junior%20in%20high%20school%20%E2%80%94%20well%20beyond%20those%20years%20where%20you're%20interacting%20with%20other%20parents%20on%20a%20regular%20basis.%20(My%20kids%20were%20both%20fine%20with%20the%20relocation%20and%20did%20swimmingly%20well%2C%20though.)%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Don't%20sell%20your%20house%20until%20you%20really%20know%20you're%20staying%20in%20your%20new%20location%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%2020%20years%20in%20my%20home%20in%20Maryland%20and%20I%20loved%20it.%20I%20also%20loved%20my%20neighbors%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20still%20among%20my%20best%20friends.%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20rented%20my%20home%20until%20I%20was%20sure%20I%20wasn't%20going%20to%20be%20returning%20to%20Maryland.%20I%20miss%20that%20house%20and%20neighborhood%20every%20single%20day%2C%20and%20renting%20it%20would%20have%20given%20me%20the%20chance%20to%20reunite%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Don't%20assume%20people%20will%20remember%20you're%20new%20in%20town%20and%20include%20you%20in%20things%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20already%20knew%20a%20few%20people%20in%20Boulder%20before%20I%20moved%20there.%20I'd%20assumed%20there%20would%20be%20more%20invites%20and%20reach%20outs%2C%20but%20people%20are%20busy%20and%20have%20their%20own%20lives.%20While%20I%20made%20a%20good%20effort%20at%20trying%20to%20connect%20with%20these%20folks%2C%20most%20didn't%20reciprocate%20very%20often.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Don't%20assume%20that%20one%20commonality%20with%20a%20place%20can%20make%20it%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20my%20time%20spent%20recreating%20outdoors%20is%20such%20a%20central%20part%20of%20my%20life%2C%20I%20assumed%20living%20near%20like-minded%20people%20was%20enough%20to%20make%20the%20move%20right.%20Life%20isn't%20one-dimensional%20and%20in%20Maryland%2C%20I%20have%20friends%20from%20all%20facets%20of%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recognize%20now%20that%20matters%2C%20at%20least%20to%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Stay%20in%20close%20contact%20with%20your%20people%20back%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20years%20I%20spent%20in%20Boulder%20were%20the%20loneliest%20I've%20ever%20experienced%2C%20and%20I%20hope%20to%20never%20go%20through%20that%20again.%20What%20kept%20me%20afloat%20were%20my%20friends%20back%20home%20in%20Maryland.%20Through%20visits%2C%20phone%20calls%2C%20and%20texts%2C%20they%20became%20a%20lifeline%20for%20me.%20It's%20so%20nice%20to%20be%20able%20to%20once%20again%20see%20them%20regularly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20want%20to%20paint%20a%20picture%20that%20I%20was%20miserable%20every%20moment%20of%20my%20time%20in%20Boulder.%20I%20did%20make%20a%20few%20friends%20through%20my%20writing%20contacts.%20Without%20intending%20to%2C%20I%20also%20met%20Mr.%20Right.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20now%20navigating%20two%20states%20and%20figuring%20out%20a%20path%20forward.%20But%20I%20can%20look%20back%20and%20recognize%20that%20here%20are%20things%20I%20definitely%20should%2C%20and%20could%2C%20have%20done%20differently.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoulder%2C%20it's%20not%20you%2C%20it's%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-maryland-boulder-colorado-loney-regret-lessons-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693475341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64efaeac0ce10a00183c033a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-maryland-boulder-colorado-loney-regret-lessons-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Moving%20to%20Boulder%2C%20Colorado%20from%20Maryland%20was%20tougher%20than%20Amanda%20Loudin%20thought.%20If%20you're%20considering%20a%20cross-country%20move%2C%20here's%20what%20she%20learned.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Loudin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-maryland-boulder-colorado-loney-regret-lessons-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Asia%20Cup%20Live