omes%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20O'Leary%20had%20a%20mix%20of%20good%20and%20bad%20news%20for%20Americans%20in%20a%20recent%20interview.%20The%20US%20economy%20has%20managed%20to%20escape%20a%20recession%20so%20far%20%E2%80%94%20but%20mortgage%20rates%20are%20headed%20higher%20in%20the%20months%20ahead%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20this%20weird%20situation%20in%20America%2C%20we're%20at%20full%20employment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%26quot%3BShark%20Tank%26quot%3B%20investor%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DvPX10zad1DQ%26t%3D79s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Fox%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20not%20yet%20seen%20the%20full%20impact%20of%20what%20should%20be%2C%20and%20has%20been%20called%20for%20for%20months%2C%20a%20recession.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20recession%20in%20America%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20strangest%20of%20times%20and%20that's%20why%20you%20should%20keep%20some%20of%20your%20powder%20dry%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20meaning%20that%20people%20should%20keep%20some%20cash%20on%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInflation%20spiked%20as%20high%20as%209.1%25%20last%20summer%2C%20spurring%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20to%20raise%20its%20benchmark%20interest%20rate%20from%20almost%20zero%20last%20spring%20to%20as%20high%20as%205.5%25%20today.%20The%20central%20bank's%20hikes%20have%20helped%20to%20slow%20price%20growth%20to%20around%203%25%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20and%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20has%20signaled%20further%20increases%20in%20the%20months%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20is%20going%20to%20stay%20vigilant%20until%20inflation's%20at%202%25%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Leary%20said.%20The%20TV%20star%20%E2%80%94%20whose%20nickname%20is%20%26quot%3BMr.%20Wonderful%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20warned%20interest%20rates%20are%20on%20track%20to%20hit%206%25%20at%