were%20coming%20on%20a%20scooter%20from%20the%20opposite%20direction%2C%20and%20the%20lane%20was%20narrow%2C%20so%20only%20one%20vehicle%20could%20pass%20at%20a%20time.%20Both%20Gill%20and%20the%20attackers%20refused%20to%20move%20back%20so%20that%20the%20other%20vehicle%20could%20pass.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shooting%20occurred%20in%20Delhi's%20Bhajanpura%20at%20around%2011.30%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20police%2C%20accused%20Bilal%20Gani%20and%20his%20associates%20Mohammad%20Sameer%20(18)%2C%20Sohail%20(23)%2C%20Mohammad%20Junaid%20(23)%2C%20and%20Adnan%20(19)%2C%20were%20partying%20in%20North%20Ghonda%2C%20Bhajanpura.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%2010.30%20pm%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20step%20out%20for%20a%20ride%20on%20two%20scooters.%20They%20stopped%20at%20a%20few%20places%20and%20finally%20started%20riding%20on%20a%20narrow%20lane%20where%20two%20bikes%20could%20not%20cross.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGani%20and%20his%20associates%20became%20aggressive%20and%20Junaid%20slapped%20Singh.%20When%20Gill%20and%20Singh%20tried%20to%20get%20down%20to%20speak%20with%20the%20youngsters%2C%20Sameer%20shot%20at%20their%20heads%2C%20the%20DCP%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20accused%20were%20identified%20after%20scanning%20CCTV%20footage%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20police%2C%20Gani%2C%20who%20worked%20at%20a%20welding%20shop%20in%20Bhajanpura%2C%20turned%2018%20on%20Sunday.%20In%202022%2C%20he%20was%20involved%20in%20a%20murder%20in%20Bhajanpura%20and%20a%20robbery%20case.%20Being%20a%20minor%20at%20that%20time%2C%20he%20managed%20to%20come%20out%20of%20the%20Children's%20Observation%20home%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693459980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F5jffl21g_amazon-manager-harpreet-gill_625x300_30_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-murder-amazon-manager-shot-dead-road-rage-behind-amazon-managers-murder-in-delhi-teen-is-prime-accused-4344222%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delhi%20Police%20today%20arrested%20an%2018-year-old%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20murder%20of%20a%20senior%20manager%20at%20Amazon.%20Harpreet%20Gill%20was%20shot%20dead%20by%20five%20people%20in%20Northeast%20Delhi%20on%20Wednesday%20when%20he%20was%20travelling%20on%20a%20bike%20with%20his%20friend.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-murder-amazon-manager-shot-dead-road-rage-behind-amazon-managers-murder-in-delhi-teen-is-prime-accused-4344222%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-murder-amazon-manager-shot-dead-road-rage-behind-amazon-managers-murder-in-delhi-teen-is-prime-accused-4344222%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-murder-amazon-manager-shot-dead-road-rage-behind-amazon-managers-murder-in-delhi-teen-is-prime-accused-4344222%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'It's%20India's%20Game%20If...'%3A%20Manjrekar's%20Big%20Claim%20Ahead%20Of%20Pakistan%20Clash%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFormer%20Indian%20cricketer%20Sanjay%20Manjrekar%20said%20that%20if%20the%20Indian%20top%20order%20consisting%20of%20Rohit%20Sharma%2C%20Shubman%20Gill%20and%20Virat%20Kohli%20gives%20Men%20in%20Blue%20a%20fine%20start%20and%20do%20not%20lose%20their%20wickets%2C%20it%20will%20be%20their%20match%20to%20win.%C2%A0%20The%20Asia%20Cup%20kickstarted%20on%20Wednesday%20with%20a%20match%20between%20Pakistan%20and%20Nepal%20in%20Multan.%20India%20will%20start%20their%20campaign%20against%20Pakistan%20in%20Kandy%20on%20September%202.%20In%20recent%20conversations%20with%20Star%20Sports%2C%20prominent%20cricket%20analysts%20Sanjay%20Manjrekar%20and%20former%20India%20cricketer%20Sanjay%20Bangar%20delved%20into%20India's%20batting%20strategies%20and%20the%20versatility%20of%20its%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experts%20highlighted%20the%20significance%20of%20India's%20top-order%20strength%20and%20the%20crucial%20role%20of%20not%20losing%20early%20wickets%20to%20secure%20successful%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManjrekar%20emphasized%20the%20test%20cricket%20skills%20needed%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%2050-over%20match%20and%20commended%20the%20defensive%20prowess%20of%20India's%20top%20three%20batters%20-%20Virat%20Kohli%2C%20Rohit%20Sharma%2C%20and%20Shubman%20Gill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManjrekar%20spoke%20on%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20top%20order%20of%20India%20and%20how%20important%20it%20is%20for%20them%20not%20to%20lose%20early%20wickets%20to%20see%20the%20match%20out%2C%20he%20said%20%26quot%3BSee%2C%20fortunately%20for%20India%2C%20number%20one%2C%20two%2C%20and%20three%2C%20when%20Virat%20bats%20at%20number%20three%2C%20they%20are%20three%20very%20good%20test%20batters.%20And%20you%20might%20talk%20about%2050%20overs%20being%20a%20one-day%20match%20and%20white-ball%20cricket%20and%20all%20that%2C%20but%20the%20start%20of%20a%2050%20overs%20game%20is%20not%20like%20a%20T20%20match.%20I%20think%20there%20are%20some%20serious%20test%20cricket%20skills%20needed%2C%20and%20then%20Rohit%20Sharma%20got%20these%20five%20hundreds%20in%20the%20last%20World%20Cup.%20I%20remember%20him%20respecting%20the%20bowling%20in%20the%20first%2010%20overs.%20And%20these%20three%20guys%20%E2%80%93%20Gill%2C%20Rohit%20Sharma%2C%20and%20Virat%20%E2%80%93%20who%20have%20excellent%20credentials%20as%20defensive%20test%20batters%2C%20that%20is%20the%20game%20they%20will%20have%20to%20bring.%20If%20they%20do%20not%20lose%20early%20wickets%2C%20then%20it%20is%20just%20their%20game.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Bangar%20shed%20light%20on%20KL%20Rahul's%20adaptable%20nature%20and%20how%20the%20team%20management%20is%20exploring%20various%20batting%20combinations%20in%20their%20training%20camp%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangar%20spoke%20on%20the%20versatility%20that%20KL%20Rahul%20brings%20to%20the%20side%20and%20how%20the%20team%20management%20is%20trying%20out%20different%20permutations%20and%20combinations%20in%20the%20batting%20line-up%20at%20the%20training%20camp%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20he%20said%20%26quot%3BKL%20Rahul%20is%20a%20very%20versatile%20player%2C%20especially%20when%20he%20is%20played%20as%20a%20batter.%20Sometimes%20he%20has%20opened%20the%20innings%2C%20sometimes%20he%20has%20batted%20at%20number%205.%20So%2C%20today%20we%20got%20to%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20in%20this%20camp.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20we%20also%20saw%20different%20pairs%20of%20players%20batting%20together%2C%20like%20as%20we%20have%20seen%20in%20yesterday's%20session%20-%20Subhman%20Gill%20and%20Rohit%20Sharma%20were%20batting%20in%20pairs.%20Today%2C%20KL%20and%20Rohit%20were%20batting%20together%20in%20pairs.%20Thus%20it%20means%20the%20team%20management%20might%20have%20this%20thought%20on%20their%20mind%20that%20whether%20KL%20Rahul%20can%20be%20utilized%20as%20an%20opening%20batsman.%20I%20do%20not%20think%20this%20is%20their%20first%20option%2C%20but%20obviously%2C%20they%20want%20to%20give%20their%20best%20chance%20for%20that%2C%20or%20they%20want%20to%20keep%20an%20option%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20concluded.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%2C%20India%20and%20Nepal%20are%20in%20Group%20A%20while%20Bangladesh%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%20are%20in%20Group%20B.%20The%20tournament%20will%20follow%20a%20hybrid%20model%20with%20Pakistan%20hosting%20four%20matches%20across%20two%20venues%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%20hosting%20the%20remaining%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20six%20group-stage%20matches%20will%20be%20followed%20by%20the%20Super%20Fours%20beginning%20September%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20will%20be%20played%20by%20the%20top%20two%20teams%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Super%20Fours%20on%20September%2017%20in%20Colombo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20Squad%3A%20Rohit%20Sharma%20(captain)%2C%20Shubman%20Gill%2C%20Virat%20Kohli%2C%20Shreyas%20Iyer%2C%20KL%20Rahul%2C%20Suryakumar%20Yadav%2C%20Tilak%20Varma%2C%20Ishan%20Kishan%2C%20Hardik%20Pandya%20(vice-captain)%2C%20Ravindra%20Jadeja%2C%20Axar%20Patel%2C%20Shardul%20Thakur%2C%20Jasprit%20Bumrah%2C%20Mohammad%20Shami%2C%20Mohammed%20Siraj%2C%20Kuldeep%20Yadav%2C%20Prasidh%20Krishna.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693459980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-11%2F7vtgv9t8_virat-kohli-rohit-sharma-afp_625x300_11_November_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fits-indias-game-if-sanjay-manjrekars-huge-prediction-ahead-of-pakistan-asia-cup-clash-4342430%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20will%20start%20their%20campaign%20against%20Pakistan%20in%20Kandy%20on%20September%202%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fits-indias-game-if-sanjay-manjrekars-huge-prediction-ahead-of-pakistan-asia-cup-clash-4342430%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fits-indias-game-if-sanjay-manjrekars-huge-prediction-ahead-of-pakistan-asia-cup-clash-4342430%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fits-indias-game-if-sanjay-manjrekars-huge-prediction-ahead-of-pakistan-asia-cup-clash-4342430%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Article%20370%20hearing%3A%20Elections%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20can%20be%20held%20at%20any%20time%2C%20Centre%20tells%20SC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693459949000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103233973%2Cimgsize-44342.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fready-for-elections-in-jammu-and-kashmir-any-time-now-centre-tells-sc-article-370%2Farticleshow%2F103233979.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20central%20government%20has%20informed%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20it%20is%20ready%20for%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20The%20process%20of%20updating%20the%20voters'%20list%20is%20currently%20underway%2C%20and%20significant%20progress%20has%20been%20made.%20The%20elections%20for%20the%20District%20Development%20Council%20have%20already%20taken%20place%2C%20and%20the%20upcoming%20Panchayat%20elections%20are%20scheduled%20to%20happen%20soon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fready-for-elections-in-jammu-and-kashmir-any-time-now-centre-tells-sc-article-370%2Farticleshow%2F103233979.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Xi%20Jinping%20to%20Skip%20G20%20Summit%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20Chinese%20Premier%20Li%20Qiang%20to%20Attend%20Instead%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F10095529%2FVladimir_Putin_and_Xi_Jinping_2019-06-05_63.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Close%20on%20the%20heels%20of%20speculation%20that%20Chinese%20president%20Xi%20Jinping%20may%20be%20giving%20the%20G20%20meet%20hosted%20by%20New%20Delhi%20a%20miss%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt%20from%20sources%20that%20it%20is%20Chinese%20premiere%20Li%20Qiang%20who%20will%20attend%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20authorities%2C%20the%20sources%20said%2C%20had%20known%20for%20a%20month%20that%20Xi%20will%20give%20the%20leaders%E2%80%99%20summit%20a%20miss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20be%20Li%E2%80%99s%20first%20visit%20to%20India%20as%20premier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20G20%20summit%20will%20be%20held%20in%20New%20Delhi%20from%20September%208%20to%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EXi%20had%20last%20visited%20India%20in%202019%20for%20the%20second%20edition%20of%20the%20informal%20summit%20at%20Mamallapuram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20he%20took%20over%20leadership%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%20has%20attended%20all%20the%20in-person%20G20%20summit%20meetings%20from%202013%20to%202019.%20After%20the%20break%20for%20COVID-19%2C%20the%20next%20physical%20summit%20meeting%20took%20place%20in%20Rome%20in%202021.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-china-58929296%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520September%252C%2520Chinese%2520officials%2520told%2520Italian%2520diplomats%2520that%2CThey%2520cited%2520China%2527s%2520Covid%2520regulations%2520as%2520the%2520reason%5C%22%3EBeijing%20had%20said%20that%20Xi%E2%80%99s%20absence%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20due%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%20own%20regulations%20on%20COVID%2C%20which%20had%20been%20highly%20restrictive.%20The%20effects%20of%20the%20pandemic%20were%20still%20lingering%20in%20many%20places%20of%20the%20world%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20no%20response%20from%20the%20Indian%20government%20on%20the%20matter%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EXi%20and%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-raised-border-stand-off-issue-in-conversation-with-xi-at-brics-says-foreign-secretary%5C%22%3Emet%20earlier%20this%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20what%20was%20their%20first%20direct%20%E2%80%98conversation%E2%80%99%20in%20over%20nine%20months%2C%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20BRICS%20Summit%20in%20South%20Africa.%20China%20later%20publicly%20claimed%20that%20the%20informal%20talks%20were%20based%20on%20an%20Indian%20request.%20India%20responded%2C%20based%20on%20sources%2C%20that%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpending%20request%E2%80%9D%20from%20China%20for%20a%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20not%20attending%2C%20it%20would%20mean%20that%20two%20heads%20of%20states%20would%20not%20be%20attending%20the%20G-20%20summit%20as%20Russian%20President%20Putin%20is%20also%20not%20attending%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20and%20India%20are%20currently%20embroiled%20in%20a%20three-year-old%20military%20stand-off%20at%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%20since%20April-May%202020.%20India%20had%20largely%20frozen%20ties%20especially%20after%20a%20clash%20in%20June%202020%20which%20led%20to%20the%20death%20of%2020%20Indian%20soldiers%20and%20at%20least%20four%20Chinese%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20%E2%80%98conversation%E2%80%99%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20Chinese%20ministry%20of%20natural%20resources%20released%20the%202023%20edition%20of%20the%20standard%20map%20of%20China%20which%20continued%20to%20show%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Aksai%20Chin%20within%20its%20boundary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20was%20a%20routine%20exercise%2C%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20release%20and%20the%20publicity%20given%20to%20it%20through%20a%20state-run%20English%20tabloid%20raised%20eyebrows%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20riled%20up%20the%20Indian%20opposition%20and%20led%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20to%20lodge%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstrong%20protest%E2%80%9D.%20China%20responded%20that%20it%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Croutine%20exercise%20of%20sovereignty%E2%80%9D%20and%20urged%20India%20to%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20over-interpret%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693459932000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F10095529%2FVladimir_Putin_and_Xi_Jinping_2019-06-05_63.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fxi-jinping-g20-li-qiang%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20will%20be%20Li's%20first%20visit%20to%20India%20as%20premier.%C2%A0%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fxi-jinping-g20-li-qiang%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Rhetoric%20of%20Akhand%20Bharat%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20Civilisational%20Claims%20in%20South%20Asia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F02234414%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-02T234320.741.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EA%20mural%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20new%20parliament%20building%20has%20become%20an%20object%20of%20controversy%20in%20South%20Asia.%20Alluding%20to%20the%20idea%20of%C2%A0%3Ci%3EAkhand%20Bharat%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20this%20ancient%20map%20appears%20to%20depict%20most%20of%20the%20current%20South%20Asian%20states%20as%20part%20of%20a%20larger%2C%20undivided%20polity%20of%20the%20past.%20Subsequently%2C%20the%20reveal%20has%20evoked%20negative%20responses%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Nepal%2C%20and%20Bangladesh.%20These%20states%20raised%20concerns%20about%20how%20the%20claims%20implied%20in%20the%20map%20threaten%20their%20independence%20and%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20a%20number%20of%20nation-states%20have%20turned%20to%20civilisational%20arguments%20to%20couch%20their%20political%20claims%2C%20drawing%20from%20a%20cultural%20invocation%20of%20the%20past%20to%20legitimise%20the%20political%20claims%20of%20the%20present.%20For%20instance%2C%20consider%20the%20relationship%20between%20civilisational%20aspirations%20and%20irredentism%2C%20i.e.%20claims%20on%20other%20nations%E2%80%99%20territories%20on%20an%20ethnic%20or%20historical%20basis.%20States%20assert%20territorial%20claims%20borrowing%20from%20a%20civilisational%20understanding%20of%20what%20its%20contours%20were%20in%20the%20past.%20Is%20India%E2%80%99s%20South%20Asia%20policy%20undergoing%20a%20paradigm%20shift%20based%20on%20civilisational%20aspirations%3F%20Is%20it%20likely%20to%20complicate%20India%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20its%20South%20Asian%20neighbours%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20March%202023%C2%A0%3Ci%3EInternational%20Affairs%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fia%2Farticle-abstract%2F99%2F2%2F475%2F7068999%3FredirectedFrom%3Dfulltext%26login%3Dfalse%5C%22%3Eresearch%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Shibashis%20Chatterjee%20and%20I%20examined%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20arguments%20in%20South%20Asia%2C%20especially%20since%202014.%20Given%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20right-wing%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20and%20the%20political%20space%20afforded%20to%20it%20by%20controlling%20a%20majority%20government%2C%20we%20asked%2C%20is%20there%20a%20Hindutva-driven%20South%20Asia%20policy%3F%20If%20indeed%20there%20is%20one%2C%20the%20core%20arguments%20espoused%20by%20the%20Hindu%20Right%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20South%20Asia%2C%20like%20the%20belief%20in%20and%20desire%20to%20restore%20Akhand%20Bharat%2C%20should%20reflect%20and%20feature%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20strategies%20for%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-idea-of-akhand-bharat-smacks-of-imperial-aspirations%5C%22%3EThe%20Idea%20of%20%E2%80%98Akhand%20Bharat%E2%80%99%20Smacks%20of%20Imperial%20Aspirations%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECivilisational%20Narratives%20and%20Official%20Conduct%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20arguments%20in%20South%20Asia%20under%20the%20BJP%20operate%20at%20two%20levels.%20At%20the%20official%20level%2C%20despite%20the%20ascendancy%20of%20the%20BJP%20regime%2C%20there%20is%20not%20a%20causal%20variable%2C%20official%20attestation%2C%20or%20endorsement%20of%20Hindutva%20in%20the%20making%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20South%20Asia%20policy.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20bilateral%20relations%2C%20India%20and%20its%20South%20Asian%20neighbours%20follow%20long-standing%20patterns%20and%20usual%20business.%20Even%20the%20current%20government%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20emphasise%20India%E2%80%99s%20exceptionalism%20through%20its%20foreign%20policy%20are%20not%20new%2C%20though%20it%20does%20put%20more%20of%20an%20emphasis%20on%20cultural%20and%20religious%20elements.%20However%2C%20this%20has%20manifested%20itself%20in%20the%20championing%20of%20spiritual%20and%20cultural%20practices%20derived%20from%20Hinduism%2C%20such%20as%20yoga%2C%20while%20steering%20clear%20of%20controversial%20issues%20like%20muscular%20nationalism%20or%20homogeneity%20of%20faith%20that%20are%20usually%20associated%20with%20the%20Hindu%20right.%20However%2C%20the%20growing%20salience%20of%20cultural%20and%20religious%20elements%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fia%2Farticle%2F93%2F1%2F7%2F2731383%5C%22%3Edoes%20not%20signify%20a%20shift%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%20the%20central%20tenets%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy.%20Cultural%20elements%20have%20been%20mostly%20about%20optics%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20engagements%20with%20the%20South%20Asian%20states%20show%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fia%2Farticle-abstract%2F93%2F1%2F27%2F2731378%5C%22%3Emore%20continuity%20than%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20denying%20the%20occasional%20rhetoric%20and%20pandering%20to%20the%20ideas%20of%20India%20as%20a%20civilisational%20state%2C%20which%20has%20important%20implications%20for%20the%20South%20Asian%20region%2C%20though%20it%20does%20not%20translate%20into%20policy.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Akhand%20Bharat%2C%20what%20this%20map%20reflects%20is%20a%20core%20civilisational%20claim%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Hindu%20Right%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20South%20Asia.%20According%20to%20this%20claim%2C%20all%20of%20modern%20South%20Asia%20is%20civilisational%20India.%20Well%20enumerated%20in%20the%20writings%20of%20Hindutva%20ideologues%20like%20Vinayak%20Damodar%20Savarkar%20and%20M.%20S.%20Golwalkar%2C%20this%20reading%20of%20history%20believes%20that%20the%20Indian%20civilisation%20was%20first%20culturally%20fractured%20by%20different%20religions%2C%20which%20finally%20resulted%20in%20territorial%20disjuncture%20through%20Partition%20in%201947.%20The%20imagery%20of%20Akhand%20Bharat%20carries%20the%20sentiment%20of%20past%20Hindu%20glory%2C%20a%20feeling%20of%20victimhood%2C%20and%20a%20resolve%20to%20reclaim%20the%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20powerful%20imagery%20notwithstanding%2C%20it%20appears%20unlikely%20to%20be%20framed%20into%20formal%20policy.%20Beyond%20the%20occasional%20romanticism%2C%20the%20most%20prominent%20spokespersons%20of%20the%20RSS%E2%80%94the%20most%20influential%20Hindu%20Right%20organisation%20that%20is%20also%20the%20ideological%20forebear%20of%20the%20ruling%20BJP%E2%80%94have%20also%20claimed%20it%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia%2Frss-calls-akhand-bharat-a-cultural-concept-not-a-political-one%2Fstory-EcuzYTNZHpqENlmawbPYYP.html%5C%22%3Ecultural%20concept%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20not%20a%20political%20one.%20Territorial%20conflicts%20with%20Pakistan%20and%20China%20remain%20alive%20despite%20Hindutva%20and%20not%20because%20of%20it.%20The%20redrawing%20of%20the%20borders%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fa-peoples-idea%2F%5C%22%3Enot%20envisaged%20by%20the%20RSS%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nor%20considered%20by%20the%20BJP%20government.%20This%20is%20primarily%20because%20the%C2%A0Akhand%20Bharat%C2%A0idea%20does%20not%20represent%20a%20policy%20for%20South%20Asia%20but%20is%2C%20instead%2C%20rhetoric%20aimed%20at%20the%20domestic%20audience%20and%20the%20Indian%20diaspora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20always%20used%20civilisational%20narratives%20as%20a%20component%20of%20its%20foreign%20policy%2C%20arguing%20for%20a%20rightful%20place%20in%20the%20world%20order.%20Its%20imagination%20of%20what%20constitutes%20civilisation%20has%20changed%20across%20Nehruvian%20and%20Hindutva%20variants.%20Hindutva%E2%80%99s%20rising%20domestic%20salience%20fits%20well%20with%20the%20narrative%20of%20a%20resurgent%20Hindu%20nation%20on%20the%20global%20stage%20reclaiming%20its%20civilisational%20space.%20Akhand%20Bharat%20remains%20a%20popular%20domestic%20narrative%20but%20does%20not%20necessarily%20show%20signs%20of%20policy%20articulation%20beyond%20this%20at%20the%20regional%20or%20international%20level.%20There%20are%20no%20indications%20of%20such%20policies%20internally%20discussed%20at%20the%20official%20level%2C%20nor%20do%20they%20find%20space%20in%20the%20dealings%20with%20South%20Asian%20states%20in%20concern%2C%20like%20Nepal%2C%20Bhutan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Sri%20Lanka.%20Unlike%20China%E2%80%99s%20claims%20in%20Taiwan%20and%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20engagements%20show%20no%20signs%20of%20territorial%20aggression%20within%20its%20neighbourhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fakhand-bharat-south-asia-politics%5C%22%3EThe%20Case%20for%20Akhand%20Bharat%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImportantly%2C%20order%20and%20stability%20in%20South%20Asia%20have%20always%20been%20crucial%20concerns%20for%20India%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20for%20its%20growth.%20Historically%2C%20the%20Indian%20state%20shows%20no%20trace%20of%20irredentism%20or%20territorial%20expansionism.%20Barring%20Pakistan%2C%20it%20has%20resolved%20boundary%20disputes%20with%20all%20of%20its%20South%20Asian%20neighbors.%20After%20all%2C%20foreign%20policy%20is%20a%20plan%20for%20the%20outside%20world%20aimed%20at%20domestic%20transformation.%20Foreign%20policy%20also%20operates%20in%20an%20international%20environment%20where%20several%20factors%20are%20at%20stake.%20Unlike%20domestic%20politics%20within%20the%20sovereign%2C%20where%20the%20governments%20have%20much%20wider%20control%2C%20the%20international%20environment%20has%20other%20states%20and%20organisations%2C%20material%20and%20ideational%20factors%2C%20laws%2C%20and%20norms%20to%20consider.%20Despite%20domestic%20political%20turnarounds%2C%20foreign%20policy%20in%20India%20has%20more%20continuity%20and%20consensus%20than%20changes.%20India%20consistently%20claims%20to%20be%20a%20responsible%20power%2C%20working%20with%20its%20neighbouring%20states%20and%20harbouring%20no%20extra-territorial%20aspirations.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20has%20resolved%20land%20and%20maritime%20boundaries%20with%20Bangladesh%20amicably.%20India%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20has%20held%20a%20committed%20stance%20on%20earlier%20issues%20of%20decolonisation%20and%20it%20articulates%20itself%20as%20a%20voice%20for%20the%20global%20south.%20Its%20rise%20as%20a%20responsible%20power%20would%20stand%20in%20conflict%20against%20such%20narratives%20of%20civilisational%20claims%20in%20South%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20silence%20or%20indifference%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20these%20narratives%20do%20not%20have%20any%20significance%20and%20implications.%20The%20conduct%20of%20foreign%20policy%20is%20not%20limited%20to%20official%20interactions%2C%20press%20releases%2C%20and%20summits.%20Complications%20persist%20in%20South%20Asia%20because%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20rhetoric%20under%20the%20BJP%2C%20even%20if%20they%20do%20not%20feature%20at%20the%20official%20level.%20Understandably%2C%20any%20claim%20of%20cultural%20superiority%20from%20India%20evokes%20emotions%20of%20insecurity%2C%20condemnation%2C%20and%20even%20imitation%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20neighbours.%20These%20exchanges%20at%20two%20levels%20often%20create%20conflicting%20perspectives%20and%20implications%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20self-image%20and%20its%20dealings%20with%20the%20South%20Asian%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20recent%20controversy%20itself.%20When%20the%20mural%20was%20revealed%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Minister%20of%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%20tweeted%2C%20%E2%80%9CResolve%20is%20clear%20%E2%80%93%20Akhand%20Bharat.%E2%80%9D%20This%20immediately%20garnered%20official%20responses%20from%20Nepal%20and%20Bangladesh.%20The%20official%20spokesperson%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%2C%20Arindam%20Bagchi%2C%20clarified%20that%20the%20mural%20showcased%20the%20past%20territorial%20landscape%20of%20the%20Iron%20Age%20Mauryan%20Empire%20and%20that%20India%20has%20no%20territorial%20aspirations%20in%20South%20Asia.%20Interestingly%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20objections%20were%20not%20brought%20up%20during%20the%20visit%20of%20its%20Prime%20Minister%20Pushpa%20Kamal%20Dahal%20to%20India%20soon%20after.%20Following%20an%20initial%20set%20of%20remarks%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20the%20issue%20did%20not%20resurface%20between%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Dhaka%20either.%20Though%20these%20objections%20did%20not%20make%20their%20way%20into%20the%20official%20policy%20space%2C%20India%20had%20to%20clarify%20and%20avert%20the%20anxieties%20of%20its%20South%20Asian%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESouth%20Asian%20Asymmetry%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20aspirations%20do%20not%20matter%20in%20regular%20bilateral%20dealings%2C%20why%20are%20these%20objections%20even%20made%3F%20There%20are%20broadly%20two%20reasons.%20The%20first%20is%20a%20structural%20factor%20of%20geographical%20and%20power%20asymmetry%20in%20South%20Asia.%20India%20looms%20large%20in%20the%20region%20and%20any%20show%20of%20power%2C%20material%20or%20cultural%2C%20raises%20anxieties%20among%20the%20South%20Asian%20states.%20Asymmetry%20is%20a%20major%20factor%20as%20to%20why%20regional%20cooperation%20in%20South%20Asia%20has%20been%20a%20difficult%20project.%20The%20second%20reason%20is%20more%20political%20in%20character.%20Just%20as%20the%20Indian%20show%20of%20civilisational%20exceptionalism%20is%20aimed%20at%20its%20own%20domestic%20audience%2C%20objections%20to%20such%20displays%20are%20also%20tied%20to%20the%20domestic%20politics%20of%20the%20other%20South%20Asian%20states.%20South%20Asian%20states%20make%20it%20a%20point%20to%20stand%20apart%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20cultural%20appropriation%20of%20the%20entire%20region%20to%20establish%20their%20exclusive%20identity.%20Against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fwebsite%2Fstory%2Fbig-brother-syndrome%2F277511%5C%22%3Eprevalent%20anti-Indian%20sentiment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20political%20players%20in%20these%20states%20see%20a%20need%20for%20independent%20and%20regular%20positioning%20that%20counters%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20arguments.%20This%20clarifies%20to%20their%20domestic%20audience%20and%20opposition%20that%20they%20are%20not%20sellouts.%20A%20tough%20stance%20against%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20claims%20helps%20the%20inward%20mobilisation%20of%20a%20distinct%20national%20identity.%20The%20objections%20follow%20and%20indicate%20deep-rooted%20ideas%20of%20exclusive%20nationalism%20from%20other%20states%20in%20South%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20claims%2C%20subtle%20or%20overt%2C%20going%20to%20impact%20its%20relations%20with%20South%20Asian%20states%3F%20Civilisational%20claims%20and%20counter-claims%20might%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20continue%20with%20the%20existing%20nature%20of%20relations%20being%20unaffected%20between%20India%20and%20South%20Asian%20states.%20Despite%20disagreements%2C%20South%20Asian%20states%20share%20legitimate%20interests%20and%20dependencies%20with%20New%20Delhi.%20These%20states%20have%20been%20pragmatic%20enough%20not%20to%20change%20their%20course%20of%20action%20toward%20India%20only%20based%20on%20civilisational%20rhetoric.%20They%20are%20likely%20to%20react%20to%20these%20occasional%20Indian%20claims%20but%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20these%20reactions%20have%20translated%20into%20policy.%20Anti-Indian%20insecurities%20along%20civilisational%20lines%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20raked%20up%20by%20South%20Asian%20states%20when%20their%20core%20interests%20suffer%20vis-a-vis%20India.%20Instances%20in%20the%20past%2C%20like%20the%20alleged%20blockade%20in%20Nepal%20or%20the%20river%20water-sharing%20issues%20with%20Bangladesh%2C%20have%20helped%20domestic%20consensus%20against%20India%20and%20overtures%20toward%20a%20balancer%20in%20China.%20India%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20claims%20and%20its%20associated%20insecurities%20are%20likely%20to%20become%20an%20instrument%20in%20such%20cases%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20South%20Asian%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EUdayan%20Das%20is%20Assistant%20Professor%2C%20Department%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20St.%20Xavier%E2%80%99s%20College%2C%20Kolkata%2C%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Fudayandas%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20in%20India%20in%20Transition%2C%20a%20publication%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2F%5C%22%3ECenter%20for%20the%20Advanced%20Study%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20(University%20of%20Pennsylvania).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693459857000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F02234414%2FUntitled-design-2023-06-02T234320.741.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fthe-rhetoric-of-akhand-bharat-and-indias-civilisational-claims-in-south-asia%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20case%20of%20Akhand%20Bharat%2C%20what%20this%20map%20reflects%20is%20a%20core%20civilisational%20claim%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Hindu%20Right%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20South%20Asia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fthe-rhetoric-of-akhand-bharat-and-indias-civilisational-claims-in-south-asia%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Adani%20Group%20rubbishes%20allegations%20of%20'opaque'%20funding%20by%20family's%20partners%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693459519000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.b