A%22For%20nearly%20seven%20months%2C%20a%20physical%20training%20(PT)%20teacher%20blackmailed%20a%2015-year-old%20student%20at%20his%20former%20school%20and%20coerced%20her%20into%20sharing%20a%20nude%20video.%20The%20teacher%20forwarded%20the%20video%20to%20two%20boys%20in%20her%20class%2C%20who%20also%20blackmailed%20her%20with%20it%2C%20extorting%20money%20from%20her.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22AVISHEK%20KUMAR%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fghaziabad%2Fgirl-blackmailed-by-former-teacher-for-7-mths-in-gzb%2Farticleshow%2F103226684.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22North%20Korea%20stages%20nuclear%20strike%20drill%20to%20protest%20allied%20exercises%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693449366000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103226651%2Cimgsize-62852.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnorth-korea-stages-nuclear-strike-drill-to-protest-allied-exercises%2Farticleshow%2F103226654.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103226654.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ENorth%20Korea%20has%20reported%20conducting%20a%20simulated%20nuclear%20strike%20on%20targets%20in%20South%20Korea%20in%20response%20to%20allied%20exercises%20that%20it%20said%20amounted%20to%20plans%20for%20a%20preemptive%20nuclear%20attack%20by%20the%20United%20States.%20The%20state%20media%20reports%20provided%20detailed%20information%20on%20how%20the%20North%20envisions%20a%20potential%20war%2C%20including%20countering%20any%20attack%20by%20striking%20the%20South%20with%20nuclear%20weapons%20and%20occupying%20its%20territory.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnorth-korea-stages-nuclear-strike-drill-to-protest-allied-exercises%2Farticleshow%2F103226654.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnorth-korea-stages-nuclear-strike-drill-to-protest-allied-exercises%2Famp_articleshow%2F103226654.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fnorth-korea-stages-nuclear-strike-drill-to-protest-allied-exercises%2Famp_articleshow%2F103226654.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Cannot%20Ignore%20the%20Tough%20Questions%20of%20Inequality%20in%20its%20Labour%20Market%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30181615%2F5319729242_621f1bdbd1_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeasured%20in%20terms%20of%20gross%20domestic%20product%20(GDP)%20growth%2C%20the%20Indian%20economy%20has%20been%20recovering%20over%20the%20past%20few%20quarters%20of%20the%20post-pandemic%20period%20though%20concerns%20remain%20over%20the%20sluggishness%20of%20the%20labour%20market.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EData%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%20(CMIE)%20showed%20that%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20continued%20to%20be%20very%20high%20at%208.5%25%20as%20of%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0August%201%2C%202023.%20When%20such%20a%20high%20unemployment%20rate%20is%20combined%20with%20a%20significant%20decline%20in%20labour%20force%20participation%20(one%20of%20the%20lowest%20in%20recent%20times%20at%2035.9%25%20in%202022-23%2C%20according%20to%20the%20CMIE)%2C%20it%20does%20not%20augur%20well%20for%20the%20prospects%20of%20the%20labour%20market%20in%20a%20country%20with%20an%20inadequate%20social%20safety%20network.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConcerns%20over%20high%20unemployment%20predate%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20The%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%20(PLFS)%20survey%202017-18%20suggested%20an%20unemployment%20rate%20of%206.1%25%20and%20pandemic-induced%20disruptions%20worsened%20the%20poor%20labour%20market%20outcome.%20The%20evidence%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiaforum.in%2Farticle%2Fhow-dynamic-are-indias-labour-markets%5C%22%3Ewell%20documented%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2FState_of_Working_India_2021-One_year_of_Covid-19.pdf%5C%22%3Erecent%20literature%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20factors%20that%20impede%20the%20recovery%20of%20the%20sluggish%20labour%20market%20require%20utmost%20attention.%20Against%20this%20backdrop%2C%20the%20release%20of%20the%20PLFS%202021-22%20report%20allows%20us%20to%20compare%20labour%20market%20dynamics%20in%20post-COVID%20compared%20with%20pre-COVID%20conditions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20PLFS%20is%20conducted%20in%20a%20July-June%20cycle.%20Since%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%20annual%20PLFS%202019-20%20survey%20experienced%20the%20full%20force%20of%20first%20wave%20of%20pandemic%20and%20all%20the%20four%20quarters%20of%202020-21%20survey%20encompassed%20both%20aftermath%20of%20the%20first%20wave%20as%20well%20as%20the%20devastating%20effects%20of%20the%20second%20wave%20(even%20if%20there%20was%20no%20national%20lockdown)%2C%20the%20present%20study%20compares%20the%20employment%20situation%20in%20the%20PLFS%202018-19%20and%202021-22%2C%20thereby%20mitigating%20any%20potential%20biases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20break%20from%20the%20earlier%20trends%20reported%20in%20both%20the%20CMIE%20and%20PLFS%20surveys%2C%20the%202021-22%20report%20shows%20improvements%20in%20the%20employment%20situation%20compared%20to%20all%20previous%20reports%20of%20the%20PLFS%2C%20which%20is%20a%20bit%20unexpected%20because%20the%20pandemic%20massively%20disrupted%20economic%20and%20social%20life.%20Based%20on%20the%20reports%2C%20the%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20(LFPR%2C%20which%20represents%20the%20number%20of%20people%20in%20the%20labour%20force%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20the%20population)%20and%20the%20worker%20population%20ratio%20(WPR%2C%20or%20the%20percentage%20of%20employed%20persons%20in%20the%20population)%20of%20those%20aged%20above%2015%20years%20increased%20from%2050.2%25%20to%2055.2%25%20and%20from%2047.3%25%20to%2052.9%25%2C%20respectively%2C%20between%202018-19%20and%202021-22.%20This%20reduced%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20from%205.8%25%20to%204.1%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20primary%20driver%20of%20this%20increase%20in%20participation%20is%20female%20participation.%20The%20rise%20in%20both%20LFPR%20and%20WPR%20is%20more%20than%208%20percentage%20points%20for%20females%20while%20they%20increased%20marginally%20by%202-3%20percentage%20points%20or%20males.%20Historically%2C%20females%20have%20had%20greater%20labour%20market%20engagement%20in%20rural%20areas%20than%20in%20urban%20areas%20%20and%20there%20was%20no%20exception%20to%20this%20even%20after%20pandemic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20those%20who%20are%2015%20years%20and%20above%2C%20the%20WPR%20of%20rural%20women%20(in%20usual%20status)%20has%20increased%20significantly%20by%2010.3%25%2C%20from%2025.5%25%20to%2035.8%20%25%2C%20with%20a%20marginal%20change%20in%20urban%20employment%20(from%2018.4%25%20to%2021.9%20%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStylised%20facts%20about%20these%20increases%20in%20participation%20raise%20the%20question%20of%20the%20workers%E2%80%99%20job%20locations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhere%20are%20the%20workers%20located%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20National%20Statistical%20Office%2C%20workers%20are%20classified%20under%20three%20broad%20categories%20%E2%80%93%20self-employed%2C%20regular%20wage%2Fsalaried%20employee%2C%20and%20casual%20labour.%20In%20urban%20areas%2C%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20females%20are%20in%20regular%20salaried%20jobs.%20But%20in%20rural%20areas%20more%20women%20fall%20into%20the%20self-employed%20category.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20pre-pandemic%202018-19%2C%2059.6%25%20of%20rural%20women%20were%20in%20self-employment%2C%20of%20which%2021.8%25%20worked%20as%20own%20account%20workers%20and%20the%20rest%20(37.9%25)%20as%20helpers%20in%20household%20enterprises%2C%20which%20were%20mostly%20unremunerative%20(Table%201).%20In%20post-pandemic%20(2021-22)%2C%20self-employment%20increased%20to%2067.8%25%20(by%20more%20than%208%25)%20for%20females%2C%20with%20proportionately%20less%20increase%20in%20own%20account%20work%20and%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20helpers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20rural%20areas%2C%20female%20participation%20as%20helpers%20is%20primarily%20as%20agricultural%20workers%20in%20family%20firms.%20Since%20agricultural%20activities%20(being%20essential%20items)%20were%20mostly%20permitted%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20lockdown%20did%20not%20much%20affect%20female%20participation%20in%20farm%20activities%20as%20helpers.%20An%20industry-wise%20classification%20confirms%20that%20female%20participation%20in%20agriculture%20is%20not%20only%20around%2070%25%3B%20it%20has%20increased%20from%2071.1%25%20to%2075.9%25%20in%20post%20pandemic%20times%20while%20male%20participation%20in%20agriculture%20reduced%20from%2053.2%25%20to%2051%25.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20pressure%20of%20reverse%20migration%2C%20male%20workers%20joined%20less%20in%20agriculture%20in%20post-pandemic.%20In%20rural%20areas%2C%20males%20were%20largely%20engaged%20in%20self-employment%20activities.%20Compared%20to%20females%2C%20within%20self-employment%2C%20there%20were%20more%20male%20own%20account%20workers%20and%20few%20helpers%20and%20there%20were%20no%20significant%20changes%20in%20participation%20in%20post-pandemic.%20In%20urban%20areas%20too%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20self-employment%20activities%20as%20a%20source%20of%20livelihood%20grew%20for%20both%20males%20and%20females%20after%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ETable%201%3A%20Percentage%20distribution%20of%20workers%20in%20usual%20status%20by%20status%20in%20employment%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20rowspan%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%223%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3ESelf-employment%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20rowspan%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3Eregular%20wage%20%2Fsalary%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20rowspan%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3Ecasual%20labour%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3Eown%20account%20workers%20and%20employers%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3Ehelper%20in%20household%20enterprise%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3Eall%20self-employment%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%225%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3ERural%20Female%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E2018-19%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E21.8%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E37.9%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E59.6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E29.3%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E2021-22%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E25.1%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E42.7%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E67.8%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E8.1%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E24.1%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%225%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3EUrban%20Female%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E2018-19%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3